            @*<h1>Birder</h1>*@
            <h2>Birder<small><i>  /ˈbəːdə/</i></small></h2>
            <h4>noun, informal</h4>
            <h4>A birdwatcher</h4>
            <hr />
            <h4>Log your bird sightings with Birder:</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Organise your observations into categories with descriptive 'tags' <i>(coming up soon)</i></li>
                <li>Upload photographs of the birds you have caught on camera <i>(coming up soon)</i></li>
            </ul>

            <br />
            <h4>Build a network of like-minded bird lovers and share what you have seen:</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>View and comment on observations from users you follow <i>(coming up soon)</i></li>
            </ul>

            <br />
            <h4>Analyse and measure your observations:</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>View your 'Life List' on the birds you have identified</li>
                <li>Earn 'badges' and increase your experience rating with 'Achievements' <i>(coming up soon)</i></li>
                <li>See a distribution map of your observations <i>(coming up soon)</i></li>
                <li>See dynamic graphs of what you have seen and when <i>(coming up soon)</i></li>
            </ul>

            <br />
            <h4>Log your observations in the field:</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>With the Android and iOS mobile apps <i>(coming up soon)</i></li>
            </ul>

